Class Pin

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xilinx.rapidwright.design.Pin
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class Pin
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    This class represents the sources and sinks found in net declarations (inpins and outpins)
    Author:
    Chris Lavin Created on: Jun 22, 2010

        private boolean isRouted
        If this is an inpin (sink), it indicates there exists routing from source to this sink. If this is a source pin it is true only if all sink pins are fully routed.
